00:12:15,519 --> 00:12:17,279
because they cannot do that and because

279
00:12:17,279 --> 00:12:19,519
they don't have your next keys, but

280
00:12:19,519 --> 00:12:22,240
because you have committed a hash of

281
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:24,959
your next keys, that rotation is already

282
00:12:24,959 --> 00:12:27,519
locked in and you can verify someone is

283
00:12:27,519 --> 00:12:29,680
legitimate controller of an identifier

284
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:32,880
without publishing the public key. This

285
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:35,519
is extremely important.

286
00:12:35,519 --> 00:12:37,680
This gives KERI something called post-

287
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:40,560
compromise recovery. Even after a key

288
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:43,519
compromise, you can regain control. And

289
00:12:43,519 --> 00:12:46,160
because of this commitment, using this

290
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,880
hash, we have resistance to future

291
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:52,079
quantum-computing attacks. There is no

292
00:12:52,079 --> 00:12:53,839
other digital identity system that

