00:12:53,839 --> 00:12:55,360
offers this level of key management

294
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,860
today.

295
00:12:57,884 --> 00:13:02,068
Multi- signature control. This ensures

296
00:13:02,092 --> 00:13:04,800
no single point of compromise for high

297
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,959
value identifiers.

298
00:13:06,959 --> 00:13:10,720
An AID can require M of N signers. For

299
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,720
example, two or three board members must

300
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:15,279
sign to rotate the organization's root

301
00:13:15,279 --> 00:13:17,839
key. The threshold can be weighted for

302
00:13:17,839 --> 00:13:20,639
governance scenarios. Rotation events

303
00:13:20,639 --> 00:13:22,399
are also respective of the threshold

304
00:13:22,399 --> 00:13:24,800
rules. This means you cannot bypass

305
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,720
multi- signature control even during a

306
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,560
rotation event.

307
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:30,800
This is critical for enterprise AIDs

308
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,639
where a single compromise no longer

309
00:13:32,639 --> 00:13:34,480
means the entire organization is now

